 icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/open\"><code>open()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/releaseInterface\"><code>releaseInterface()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/reset\"><code>reset()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/selectAlternateInterface\"><code>selectAlternateInterface()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/selectConfiguration\"><code>selectConfiguration()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/transferIn\"><code>transferIn()</code></a></li><li><svg class=\"icon icon-experimental\" tabindex=\"0\">\n    <use xlink:href=\"/assets/badges.svg#icon-experimental\"></use>\n</svg><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/transferOut\"><code>transferOut()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for WebUSB API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USB\"><code>USB</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBAlternateInterface\"><code>USBAlternateInterface</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBConfiguration\"><code>USBConfiguration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBConnectionEvent\"><code>USBConnectionEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBEndpoint\"><code>USBEndPoint</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBInTransferResult\"><code>USBInTransferResult</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBInterface\"><code>USBInterface</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBIsochronousInTransferPacket\"><code>USBIsochronousInTransferPacket</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBIsochronousInTransferResult\"><code>USBIsochronousInTransferResult</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket\"><code>USBIsochronousOutTransferPacket</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBIsochronousOutTransferResult\"><code>USBIsochronousOutTransferResult</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBOutTransferResult\"><code>USBOutTransferResult</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard experimental\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Experimental:</strong> <strong>This is an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/MDN/Writing_guidelines/Experimental_deprecated_obsolete#experimental\">experimental technology</a></strong><br>Check the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">Browser compatibility table</a> carefully before using this in production.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>clearHalt()</code></strong> method of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice\"><code>USBDevice</code></a>\n  interface returns a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>promise</code></a> that resolves when a halt condition is\n  cleared. A halt condition is when a data transfer to or from the device has a status\n  of <code>'stall'</code>, which requires the web page (the <em>host</em> system, in USB\n  terminology) to clear that condition. See the for details.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">clearHalt(direction, endpointNumber)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"direction\"><code>direction</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Indicates whether the devices input or output should be cleared. Valid values\n      are <code>'in'</code> or <code>'out'</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"endpointnumber\"><code>endpointNumber</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Indicates the number of the endpoint to clear. The promise will reject if an invalid\n      endpoint is supplied.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>promise</code></a>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>\n  The following example shows how to test for and clear a <code>'stall'</code> condition\n  in the result of a data transfer.\n</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>Note:</strong> What data can be passed to a USB device and how it is passed is particular and unique\n    to each device.\n  </p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">while</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token boolean\">true</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> result <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> data<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">transferIn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data <span class=\"token operator\">&amp;&amp;</span> result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>byteLength <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token number\">6</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Channel 1: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getUint16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Channel 2: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getUint16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">log</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span><span class=\"token string\">Channel 5: </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>data<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getUint16</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">4</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token template-punctuation string\">`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>result<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>status <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'stall'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    console<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">warn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Endpoint stalled. Clearing.'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> device<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">clearHalt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'in'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/webusb/#ref-for-dom-usbdevice-clearhaltâ‘ ","title":"WebUSB API"}],"query":"api.USBDevice.clearHalt"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.USBDevice.clearHalt","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/clearHalt/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The clearHalt() method of the USBDevice\n  interface returns a promise that resolves when a halt condition is\n  cleared. A halt condition is when a data transfer to or from the device has a status\n  of 'stall', which requires the web page (the host system, in USB\n  terminology) to clear that condition. See the for details.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T06:39:07.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/usbdevice/clearhalt","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/usbdevice/clearhalt/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/b9bcca1e96839aa9cddea3263196e0cf4656d387","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice","title":"USBDevice"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/USBDevice/clearHalt","title":"USBDevice.clearHalt()"}],"pageTitle":"USBDevice.clearHalt() - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}